data.name: Optimal Charge Window Size
data.description: Size of the green zone. Bigger = easier to stay within it and fracture successfully.

data.description: Speed at which the optimal (green) zone shifts during charging. Affects how steady you need to be.

data.name: Laser Instability

data.name: Resistance
data.description: Alters rock resistance. Higher resistance = more laser power needed.

data.name: Instability
data.description: Adds or reduces the rock’s instability stat. Lower = more stable = easier to control charge.

data.name: Cluster Modifier
data.description: Multiplier to how many chunks a rock breaks into. Affects post-fracture collectability.

data.name: Optimal Range
data.description: Ideal distance from the rock for the gadget’s effect to be strongest.

data.name: Maximum Range
data.description: How far from the rock you can place/activate the gadget.

data.description: Boosts the strength of your mining laser.

data.name: Extraction Laser Power
data.description: Affects extraction phase power — useful when pulling in fractured materials.
